ory: This is a bug."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2020-06-10T16:26:04Z", "updated_at": "2020-06-28T17:51:52Z", "closed_at": "2020-06-28T17:51:51Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Couldn't find a way to enable `trivial_casts` for the following use-case. Maybe there are another ways to make a successful compilation? \r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![forbid(trivial_casts)] // Remove lint and code will compile\r\n\r\nuse core::fmt::Debug;\r\n\r\nfn stuff<'a, D, FROM, TO>(from: &'a FROM) -> TO\r\nwhere\r\n    D: Debug + 'a,\r\n    FROM: AsRef<[D]>,\r\n    TO: AsRef<[&'a dyn Debug]> + Default + Extend<&'a dyn Debug>\r\n{\r\n    let mut to: TO = Default::default();\r\n    // Remove cast and code won't compile\r\n    // Bind value ref to a tmp variable and lifetime issues will appear\r\n    to.extend(from.as_ref().iter().map(|value| value as &_));\r\n    to\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let from_array = [1, 2, 3];\r\n    let _to_vec_with_obj_refs: Vec<_> = stuff(&from_array);\r\n}\r\n```", "closed_by": {"login": "c410-f3r", "id": 17877264, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3ODc3MjY0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17877264?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r", "html_url": "https://github.com/c410-f3r", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.gi